About
The museum reveals the secrets to the perfume trade, as well as a collection of precious objects tracing the history of perfume from antiquity to the present day. Immersed in the atmosphere of a late nineteenth century perfume factory, visitors will discover the world of fragrance through a set design that combines ancient artefacts, archives and videos of modern production.
Duration: < 1 hour

I wouldn’t recommend this to anyone who want really learn about parfum and make your own parfum.
Oct 2024 • Family
The initial explanation was rushed, leaving everyone in the room confused. The order of the activities didn't make sense either: we first made a perfume, then learned about the history of perfume. This left us with many unanswered questions about how perfume is actually made.

The process was also disappointing—we merely modified an existing fragrance from the brand by adjusting the percentages of just three pre-selected essences. The result was a perfume that was unpleasant and completely unusable.

Everyone had numerous questions throughout the experience, but the fast pace of the tour made it impossible to get any clarification.

To make things worse, the entire activity was done standing up, with the perfume being mixed on a bench. There was no opportunity to sit comfortably and focus on the experiment.

At the end of the experience, the brand takes you to a separate area where they try to sell you their own perfumes. If you're looking to create your own unique fragrance, this experience is not for you. They claim that simply adjusting the percentage of pre-chosen notes makes the perfume 'yours' and unique, but in reality, you don't get to choose the essences.

I wouldn’t recommend this to anyone and would definitely suggest looking for a better experience elsewhere

Dear Sir, Dear Madam, Thank you for taking the time to share with us your feedback following your participation in our Flower of the Year Workshop. We are sorry to hear it wasn’t what you expected. This workshop is a true initiation to the olfactory pyramid, as you discover 3 compositions of blended essences that go into the creation of this Flower of the Year fragrance which is Lilac. In 20 minutes, you personalize your own Flower of the Year in the form of a 12ml eau de toilette, and discover its history, origins, culture and use in perfumery. Our workshops are always paired with a guided tour of the establishment. As you can see on our website (where you probably booked your workshop), you have all those informations about it. There is the link : https://musee-parfum-paris.fragonard.com/en/book-your-workshop/?re-product-id=194671&rwstep=product As we are constantly striving to improve the experience we offer, please do not hesitate to contact us directly at reviews@fragonard.com with any recommendations you may have regarding the workshop you attended. Make your very own perfume to take home
Aug 2024 • Couples
A truly memorable experience where we got to prepare our own unique eau de parfumerie under the direction of an expert perfumer. Learned a lot too about what goes into preparing various scents. The place is away from the main town of Grasse and we took a Uber to reach it. The guided visit to the shop after the museum tour was very stylishly done where we were introduced to different fragrances and other products. Overall, this was a highlight of the south of France trip. I highly recommend it as you leave with a bottle of your own creation ensconced in a small drawstring sack - perfect memento of your nasal creativity!

Dear Madam, Dear Sir, We thank you for taking the time to share your experience and we are sincerely sorry to read that the welcome you received did not live up to your expectations. At Fragonard, for almost a century, we have been committed to delivering and developing a customer experience in line with our quality standards and values. In that sense, our Google rate of 4.4/5 with over 5300 reviews is a result of the special attention we pay to the welcome we provide to our visitors. You've taken part in one of our free guided tours, which in 30 minutes, covers the secrets of perfume making (raw materials, harvesting, extraction, distillation, formulation, bottling), the creative process and the job of the nose, as well as the perfume’s history, illustrated by a unique collection of antiques assembled by the founding family of our House. The tour ends with an olfactory discovery of our creations, all traditionally produced in our factories in Eze-Village and Grasse, the world capital of perfume. We invite you to contact us at reviews@fragonard.com to understand your detailed comments and share them with the relevant team with the aim of ensuring a welcome that lives up to our standards. Great fun
Visited with my two daughters and my 10 year old granddaughter and we had a great time. The make your own perfume workshop is pretty basic but we had a lot of fun mixing the different notes and comparing our resulting fragrances with each other. The workshop was followed by a very interesting tour of the museum and history of perfume and then we were in the shop where we got to smell a bunch of Fragonard fragrances and purchase some if we desired. Of course we desired! The fragrance I chose to purchase smells so good and honestly lasts way longer than perfumes usually do on me!

This was one of my granddaughter's favorite activities in Paris. Well worth the time and price!
